  m_text: "In solid geometry, a sphere is the set of points that are all at the same
    distance <i>r</i> from a given point in three-dimensional space. That given point
    is the center of the sphere, and the distance <i>r</i> is the sphere's radius.
    \n\n<b>Formula: V = (4/3)\u03C0r<sup>3</sup></b>"
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
